Dialogue: 5,0:12:22.51,0:12:24.72,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{And that's this Galley-La Company.}That's the Galley-La Company.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:25.40,0:12:28.60,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{His passion and skills \Nin shipbuilding have never changed,}His passion and skill for shipbuilding hasn't waned,
Dialogue: 5,0:12:28.60,0:12:31.85,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,and {the craftsmen won't forget \Ntheir respect towards him.}he's never lost \Nthe respect of the shipwrights.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:31.85,0:12:34.90,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{And, because the craftsmen \Nare proud of their skills,}And, because the craftsmen \Ntake pride in their skills,
Dialogue: 5,0:12:34.90,0:12:38.44,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,they {never}neither give in to pirates {or}nor authority.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:39.40,0:12:42.00,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{This is that kind of place.}That's how things run here.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:42.00,0:12:42.86,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Hmm?
Dialogue: 5,0:12:42.86,0:12:46.30,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Hey, {pops}old guy.\NI heard {that }you're a top-notch shipwright.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:46.30,0:12:48.12,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Do you wanna}Wanna be a pirate with me?
Dialogue: 5,0:12:48.12,0:12:50.44,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{What the hell are you saying, \Nyou son of a bitch?!}Wanna run that by us again, jackass?!
Dialogue: 5,0:12:50.44,0:12:51.60,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{H-How insolent!}H-How brazen!
Dialogue: 5,0:12:51.60,0:12:53.93,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Now, now... He's always like that.}Well, y'know{... H}, he's always like this.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:53.93,0:12:55.00,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Sorry about that.}Sorry 'bout that.
